stories.text: I've lost count on how many independent news orgs have said their news stories have been demonetized or blocked because of some made up reason by YouTube. Then YouTube will gladly run corporate news videos from CNN or MSNBC that use the same video from the independent news org. This is quite obvious collusion between YouTube and the major corporate news orgs. Also they are blocking stories that make people in power uneasy.

stories.text:
I am dev with 6+ years of experience.

What is happening to the dev market? I can't help but notice a trend.

On twitter, I see 17 year old devs pulling in 120k+ annual income [1].

At 17, I had not even started my college yet.

Is this the new normal?

It all seems to be a bit surreal seeing teenagers make so much money in high school while they struggle to even make a proper git commit.

[1] https://twitter.com/PrasoonPratham/status/1468899558289592322
